        "Because the sides are parallel, the transformation is doing something very simple: it stretches by 2 in the horizontal direction, and stretches by 3 in the diagonal direction. That's it. No rotation, no shearing. Just two stretchings. This is what makes it an **eigenbasis**.\n",
